#include <linux/kernel.h>
#include <linux/init.h>
#include <linux/module.h>

#include <linux/miscdevice.h>
#include <linux/slab.h>
#include <linux/uaccess.h>
#include <linux/interrupt.h>
#include <linux/wait.h>
#include <linux/timer.h>
#include <linux/jiffies.h>
#include <linux/platform_device.h>
#include <linux/of.h>
#include <linux/of_gpio.h>
#include <linux/gpio.h>
#include <linux/delay.h>
#include <linux/workqueue.h>
#include <linux/sched.h>
const int Gapvalue = 430;
static int first_weight;
struct HZ711{
	int sck_gpio;
	int dt_gpio;
};
struct HZ711 * hz711;
long HZ711_Read(void)
{
	long count = 0;
	int i;
	mdelay(10);
	gpio_set_value(hz711->sck_gpio, 0);
	while(gpio_get_value(hz711->dt_gpio));
	for(i=0; i<24; i++)
	{
		gpio_set_value(hz711->sck_gpio, 1);
		if(i != 0)
			count = count<<1;
		udelay(25);
		gpio_set_value(hz711->sck_gpio, 0);
		if(gpio_get_value(hz711->dt_gpio))
			count++;
		udelay(25);
	}
	gpio_set_value(hz711->sck_gpio, 1);
	count=count^0x800000;
	udelay(25);
	gpio_set_value(hz711->sck_gpio, 0);
	return count;
}
int Get_Weight(void)
{
	int Weight;
	Weight = (long)HZ711_Read();
	Weight = (long)(Weight - first_weight);
	if(Weight < 0)
		Weight = (- Weight);
	Weight = (int)(Weight / Gapvalue);
	return Weight;
}
static int hz711_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
{
	enum of_gpio_flags dt_flag;
	enum of_gpio_flags sck_flag;
	hz711 = kmalloc(sizeof(struct HZ711), GFP_KERNEL);
	if(!hz711)
	{
		printk("hz711 kmalloc memory err!!!\n");
		return -ENODEV;
	}
	hz711->sck_gpio = of_get_named_gpio_flags(pdev->dev.of_node, "sck-gpio", 0, &sck_flag);
	if(!gpio_is_valid(hz711->sck_gpio))
	{
		printk("sck-gpio is invalid!\n");
		return -ENODEV;
	}
	gpio_direction_output(hz711->sck_gpio, 0);
	hz711->dt_gpio = of_get_named_gpio_flags(pdev->dev.of_node, "dt-gpio", 0, &dt_flag);
	if(!gpio_is_valid(hz711->dt_gpio))
	{
		printk("dt-gpio is invalid!\n");
		return -ENODEV;
	}
	gpio_direction_input(hz711->dt_gpio);
	if(gpio_request(hz711->sck_gpio, "sck-gpio"))
	{
		printk("request sck-gpio faild!!!\n");
		gpio_free(hz711->sck_gpio);
			return -1;
	}
	if(gpio_request(hz711->dt_gpio, "dt-gpio"))
	{
		printk("request dt-gpio faild!!!\n");
		gpio_free(hz711->dt_gpio);
			return -1;
	}
	first_weight = (long)HZ711_Read();
	return 0;
}
static int hz711_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *filp)
{
//	schedule_delayed_work(&work, 1*HZ);
	return 0;
}
static int hz711_release(struct inode *inode, struct file *filp)
{
	return 0;
}
ssize_t hz711_read(struct file *filp, char __user *buf, size_t size, loff_t *f_pos)
{
	int ret, Weight;
	char Weight_buf[20] = {0};
	Weight = Get_Weight();
	if(Weight >= 5000)
        {
                ret = copy_to_user(buf, "Overweight!(5000g)", sizeof("Overweight!(5000g)"));
                return ret;
        }
	sprintf(Weight_buf, "%d", Weight);
	ret = copy_to_user(buf, Weight_buf, 10);
	return ret;
}
static struct file_operations hz711_fops = {
	.owner = THIS_MODULE,
	.open  = hz711_open,
	.release = hz711_release,
	.read  = hz711_read,
};
static struct miscdevice hz711_miscdev = {
	.minor = MISC_DYNAMIC_MINOR,
	.name  = "HZ711",
	.fops  = &hz711_fops,
};
static int hz711_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
{
	kfree(hz711);
	return 0;
}
static const struct of_device_id hz711_match[] = {
	{ .compatible = "avia,hx711" },
	{},
};
static struct platform_driver hz711_driver = {
	.probe = hz711_probe,
	.remove = hz711_remove,
	.driver = {
		.owner = THIS_MODULE,
		.name = "hz711_Pressure_transducer",
		.of_match_table = hz711_match,
	}
};
static int hz711_init(void)
{
	platform_driver_register(&hz711_driver);
	return misc_register(&hz711_miscdev);
}
static void hz711_exit(void)
{
	platform_driver_unregister(&hz711_driver);
	return ;
}
module_init(hz711_init);
module_exit(hz711_exit);
MODULE_DESCRIPTION("HZ711 Pressure transducer");
MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");

}
